    {
      "type": "text",
      "title": "RTSP Streams & Video Panel",
      "gridPos": { "x": 12, "y": 0, "w": 12, "h": 10 },
      "options": {
        "content": "## Viewing RTSP streams\n\nTo view RTSP streams directly in Grafana you need a video panel plugin that can render or proxy RTSP (for example `grafana-video-panel` or a similar plugin).\n\nRTSP URL example: `rtsp://<host>:9192/<topic>` (use the subscribe port configured for your rtsper instance).\n\nIf your Grafana host cannot directly access RTSP endpoints due to NAT/firewall you can run a small proxy that converts RTSP -> HLS or MJPEG and render that URL in Grafana's Image or Video panels.\n\nNote: Installing a third-party plugin requires admin permissions on the Grafana server."
      }
    }
